name: Kitty Tuna Dreams
author: Rene Bradley
summary: Your feline friends will find these kitty treats purr-fect. Tuna is mixed with eggs, bread crumbs, and brewer's yeast and baked into tasty biscuits that are delicious and nutritious.
ingredients: 1 teaspoon vegetable oil, or more as needed
2 cups canned low-sodium tuna in oil
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Lightly grease a baking sheet with vegetable oil
Drain tuna and reserve oil; add enough vegetable oil to make 1/4 cup total
Combine tuna, reserved oil, bread crumbs, eggs, and brewer's yeast in a bowl
Drop 1/4 teaspoonfuls of tuna mixture 1 inch apart onto the prepared baking sheet
Bake in the preheated oven until set, about 10 minutes
Cool biscuits and store covered in the refrigerator
